---

## Pre-DR Capture Requirements

Capture and save all outputs into timestamped folders.

Example:

DR_PRE_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS

Collect:

### Cluster Information

* Current cluster
* Logged-in user
* Current project/namespace

Commands to use:

* oc whoami
* oc project
* oc status

### Pods

Capture:

* Pod name
* Status
* Ready count
* Restart count
* Node
* Creation timestamp
* Pod age

Commands:

* oc get pods -o wide
* oc get pods --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp

### Deployments

Capture:

* Ready replicas
* Available replicas
* Desired replicas

Commands:

* oc get deployment
* oc describe deployment

### StatefulSets

Capture all StatefulSets.

### Services

Capture:

* Service names
* Cluster IP
* Ports
* Target ports

Commands:

* oc get svc -o wide
* oc get svc -o yaml

### Routes

Capture:

* Hostnames
* TLS configuration
* Target services

Commands:

* oc get routes
* oc get routes -o yaml

### ConfigMaps

Capture all ConfigMaps.

### Secrets References

Capture deployment references to:

* Secrets
* ConfigMaps
* Volumes

Do not capture actual secret values.

### Resource Usage

Commands:

* oc adm top pods
* oc adm top nodes

### Events

Capture:

* All events
* Sorted by timestamp

Commands:

* oc get events --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp

### Node Placement

Capture:

* Which node every pod is running on

Purpose:

* Verify workload migration after DR

### Logs

Capture last 30 minutes from each deployment.

Commands:

* oc logs deployment/<deployment> --since=30m

